# Compliance Engine

## Purpose

Evaluate endpoint compliance against one or more regulatory frameworks and produce standardized compliance scores, evidence, and remediation recommendations.

---

## Inputs

- STIG Checklists
- SCAP Results
- PowerShell Control Validation
- Registry Values
- Group Policy Results
- Asset Inventory
- Security Baseline Definitions

---

## Processing

- Validate implemented controls.
- Map findings to NIST SP 800-53, NIST SP 800-171, ISO 27001, CMMC Level 2, or other supported frameworks.
- Eliminate duplicate findings.
- Calculate compliance percentages by control family.
- Associate evidence with each control.
- Generate remediation tasks for failed controls.

---

## Outputs

- Compliance Workbook
- Control Status Report
- Evidence Repository
- Compliance Score
- Failed Control List
- Executive Metrics

---

## Metrics

|Metric|Description|
|---|---|
|Overall Compliance|Percentage of implemented controls|
|Control Family Score|Compliance by NIST control family|
|Failed Controls|Number of controls requiring remediation|
|Evidence Coverage|Percentage of controls with supporting artifacts|
|Framework Coverage|Number of supported compliance frameworks|

